Confirmed in the latest master dbb69412e56ebd66e3a88a0589c5f061db496269. (this issue seems not so new thogh)

I made a small test https://github.com/yTakatsukasa/verilator/commit/acdfb1b07c80de35ae96686245d6ca6f6673c856 in  https://github.com/yTakatsukasa/verilator/tree/unpack_slice.

```systemverilog
module t (
   clk
   );
   input clk;

   // unpack_sig0[6] and unpack_sig1[6] are expected to have the
   // same value regard less of their extent
   logic unpack_sig0 [0:6];
   logic unpack_sig1 [3:6];

   always @(posedge clk) begin
      unpack_sig0[3] <= 1'b1;
      unpack_sig1[3] <= 1'b1;
      unpack_sig0 [4:6] <= unpack_sig0[3:5];
      unpack_sig1 [4:6] <= unpack_sig1[3:5];
   end

   int c = 0;
   always @(posedge clk) begin
      c <= c + 1;
      if (c == 4) begin
         if (!unpack_sig0[6] || !unpack_sig1[6]) $stop;
         $write("*-* All Finished *-*\n");
         $finish;
      end else begin
         if (unpack_sig0[6] || unpack_sig1[6]) $stop;
      end
   end
endmodule
```

`unpack_sig0` and `unpack_sig1` are used in the same way. The only difference is existence of unused extent of `[0:2]`.
The value of `unpack_sig0` and `unpack_sig1` are different.
C++ compiler shows warnings for Verilated code as below.
```
In file included from Vt__ALL.cpp:3:
./Vt.cpp:103:43: warning: array index 4 is past the end of the array (which contains 4 elements) [-Warray-bounds]
    __Vdlyvval__t__DOT__unpack_sig1__v2 = vlTOPp->t__DOT__unpack_sig1
                                          ^
```

I suspect V3WidthSel.cpp, but not yet found where to fix.
